    "We preserve the values used in the form along with the feedback (both inline and global) for generating assertions in the subsequent test generation phase.After iterating through these steps for every input field and each associated constraint, we accumulate a database comprising discrepancies, submission success, and submission errors.",
    "Test GenerationThe overarching objective of our test generation is to cover a comprehensive range of form submission states, inclusive of both successful and failed form submissions.",
    "Each test case examines a submission state of the form-under-test (See Definition 1).Throughout the prior stages, we have generated and validated anticipated constraints for each input field.",
    "We expect these constraints to correspond to a potential execution scenario within the form's functionality.",
    "By submitting values that either adhere to or violate each constraint, we are effectively verifying the presence of the associated execution scenarios within the form's logic."
